 FRSC  FRSC Commander in Benue, David Mendie, disclosed this in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Saturday in Makurdi. He said the command was prepared and ready to handle all traffic related matters during the president’s visit. Read More: Buhari returns to Abuja, joins Muslim faithful to observe prayer He said the number of personnel deployed to locations in the state would depend on the presidential entourage. Mendie said plans would be concluded when they were furnished with the president’s itinerary. “We will provide alternative routes for motorists, especially on routes earmarked for the president,” he said.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .